article.headline: Rhode Island 54, Miami 53
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Brian Woodward scored 13 points and Rhode Island withstood two potentially game-winning shots in the final five seconds to defeat Miami, 54-53, in a third-round game of the NCAA Las Vegas Tournament Tuesday. Miami's Armondo Surratt missed a 3-pointer with five seconds left and teammate Darius Rice made a 3-pointer just after the buzzer had sounded. The Rams (2-1) went ahead, 50-48, when Woodward made two free throws at 3:28. Rhode Island increased its lead to 52-48 on Dustin Hellenga's lay-up at 3:01. Robert Hite scored to narrow the lead to 52-50 for Miami (2-1), but a basket by Woodward gave the Rams a 54-50 advantage with 1:05 remaining. A 3-pointer by Hite with 50 seconds left cut the Rams' lead to 54-53. Rhode Island led 30-19 going into the last minute of the first half but consecutive 3-pointers by the Hurricanes' Karron Clarke and Rice brought Miami within five, 30-25. Rice led the Hurricanes with 12 points.
